cinnamon.engine.utils

Interface SpacePartitioningTree<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - element to partition.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LockingSpacePartitioningTree<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryBVH

    public interface SpacePartitioningTree<E>

    Organizes elements by a corresponding Bounds' location and volume to perform containment and intersection queries. Added Bounds-element pairs must be updated should changes to a Bounds' size or position invalidate its place in the tree.

    Containment and intersection queries are provided in two flavors to return either a List or an array. The latter variant is intended for queries where iteration over the results is the main operation and it is expected to occur frequently.

    Implementations disallowing a Bounds-element pair from being added to the tree may throw an IllegalArgumentException.

      • equals

        boolean equals(Object object)

        Returns true if either the given object is the same tree instance or the following conditions are met.

        • The given object is also a SpacePartitioningTree and both trees have the same size.
        • Each Bounds-element pair has a corresponding pair in the other tree whose Bounds and element are equivalent in the following expression bounds.equals(otherBounds) && element.equals(otherElement).
        Overrides:

        Parameters:

      • hashCode

        int hashCode()

        The hash code is computed as if by the following.

             
         for (pair : content) {
             int pairHash = initial * 31 + pair.bounds.hashCode();
             pairHash = 31 * pairHash + pair.element.hashCode();

             treeHash = 31 * treeHash + pairHash;
         }
